#### 6. Explain what an "event" is (within the context of a webpage).

//Your Answer
An event is when something interactive occurs on the page. This can have a JS action attached to it which acts as a event listener and will execute once the specified event takes place.
//Googled Answer

#### 7. What's the difference between =, ==, and === in JavaScript?

//Your Answer
= is used for declaring. == is equal but not as strict in terms of data types as ===

//Googled Answer


